						               													<description>The entity known as Chaos began the formation of a new planet an attracted the attention of the whole cosmos. From every corner of the universe, the gods of creation came together for a big competition!&amp;#10;&amp;#10;In Deusastrados, players assume the role of these gods, striving to fulfill the orders of Chaos and generate the best and most adapted creatures to populate the new planet.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Rounds in Deusastrados are divided into four phases:&amp;#10;&amp;#10;CREATION&amp;#10;Players, in real-time and simultaneously, draw creature parts cards from the center of the table and use them to build their creatures, or to sabotage their opponents' creatures.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;POWERS&amp;#10;Players check their god's available power cards and choose one to lay face-down on the table. All of them are revealed simultaneously and they are activated in order of priority.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;CHAOS&amp;#10;All creatures with parts unwanted by Chaos discard those parts.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;SCORING&amp;#10;The remaining creatures and parts score, following the rules.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Deusastrados has a basic mode and an asymmetrical one, in which each god has his own ability and distinct powers.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
